86
00:04:38,971 --> 00:04:41,460
This is the case of 
a simple deterministic approach

87
00:04:41,460 --> 00:04:44,713
that can be used 
to analyze translational slides.

88
00:04:44,713 --> 00:04:46,623
It applies to shallow soil covers,

89
00:04:46,623 --> 00:04:49,282
or existing discontinuities 
parallel to the slope

90
00:04:49,282 --> 00:04:51,862
when the length of the landslide body

91
00:04:51,862 --> 00:04:55,304
is much higher than the thickness of it.

92
00:04:55,304 --> 00:04:56,816
Translational failure mechanism

93
00:04:56,816 --> 00:04:59,034
with surface of rupture 
parallel to the slope,

94
00:04:59,034 --> 00:05:02,596
can be analyzed thanks to 
the infinite slope model.

95
00:05:02,596 --> 00:05:05,095
Thanks to the elongated shape 
of the landslide body,

96
00:05:05,095 --> 00:05:07,914
we can make the hypothesis 
of an infinite slope.

97
00:05:07,914 --> 00:05:10,786
We can isolate a portion of the slope,

98
00:05:10,786 --> 00:05:14,057
and write all the forces 
which are applied on it,

99
00:05:14,057 --> 00:05:16,777
starting from the weight,
considering the forces

100
00:05:16,777 --> 00:05:20,008
which are coming from 
the interaction of the isolated mass

101
00:05:20,008 --> 00:05:23,626
from the surrounding masses,
and the resulting forces,

102
00:05:23,626 --> 00:05:26,438
which are coming from the pore water
pressure distribution

103
00:05:26,438 --> 00:05:28,318
inside the landslide body.

104
00:05:28,918 --> 00:05:33,399
The ratio between the resisting force
and the destabilizing force

105
00:05:33,399 --> 00:05:35,799
give us the factor of safety.

106
00:05:35,799 --> 00:05:40,132
The factor of safety is a very clever way
to define and to assess

107
00:05:40,132 --> 00:05:42,119
the stability condition
of a given slope.

108
00:05:42,119 --> 00:05:43,559
The higher this number,

109
00:05:43,559 --> 00:05:48,309
it means that we are far 
from a possible failure of the slope.

110
00:05:48,309 --> 00:05:51,950
In this slide, we see how 
